<HL>
   Marketing Brief -- Pathe Communications Corp.:
   Concern Reports 1st-Quarter
   Net Income of $46.4 Million
</HL>
<DATE>
05/07/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4
</SO>
<CO>
   PCC
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Pathe Communications Corp. reported first-quarter net
income of $46.4 million, or 77 cents a share, compared with
$10.3 million, or 91 cents, a year earlier. The number of
outstanding common shares rose to 59.7 million, from 11.4
million.
   The results include a $50.1 million gain from the sale of
certain European movie theaters that the Los Angeles-based
company now operates. An additional $30 million gain will be
recorded later this year, the company said. The 1990 results
also list extraordinary gains of $18 million from an
extinguishment of debt and utilization of tax loss
carryforwards. The year-ago quarter included an extraordinary
gain of $23.9 million for repurchase of subordinated debt.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Revenue was $76.6 million, compared with $91.8 million a
year ago. Pathe President Giancarlo Parretti said, "The
upcoming introduction of our first slate of films will have
an extremely positive financial impact on our company."
Pathe's first film is scheduled to be released this summer.
   Pathe is currently engaged in a $1.26 billion cash tender
offer for MGM/UA Communications Co., which could, with
extensions, continue until June 23. A third $50 million down
payment is due May 17.
</TEXT>
